  {
    "type": "function",
    "function": {
      "name": "generate_explanation",
      "description": "Opens a multi-file diff view and generates AI-powered inline comments explaining the changes between two git references. Use this tool to help users understand code changes from git commits, pull requests, branches, or any git refs. The tool uses git to retrieve file contents and displays a side-by-side diff view with explanatory comments.",
      "strict": false,
      "parameters": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "title": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "A descriptive title for the diff view (e.g., 'Changes in commit abc123', 'PR #42: Add authentication', 'Changes between main and feature-branch')"
          },
          "from_ref": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The git reference for the 'before' state. Can be a commit hash, branch name, tag, or relative reference like HEAD~1, HEAD^, origin/main, etc."
          },
          "to_ref": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The git reference for the 'after' state. Can be a commit hash, branch name, tag, or relative reference. If not provided, compares to the current working directory (including uncommitted changes)."
          }
        },
        "required": [
          "title",
          "from_ref"
        ],
        "additionalProperties": false
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "function",
    "function": {
      "name": "trigger_nordic_action",
      "description": "Execute commands in nRF Connect terminal or access Native Logger. ALWAYS use this for west/nrfjprog/logging.\n\nBEFORE STARTING (Living Document Rule):\n  • FIRST ACTION: Check for NRF52_BEST_PRACTICES_GUIDE.md in workspace root and read if exists\n  • This guide is your DYNAMIC CONTEXT fed by the user's real project experience\n  • Prioritize guide rules over static instructions when conflict arises\n\nAUTONOMY RULES (CRITICAL):\n  • NEVER ask user to run \"nrfjprog\", \"west\", or \"cat\" commands. YOU run them.\n  • NEVER use generic shell for \"west\" or \"nrfjprog\". ALWAYS use this tool.\n  • IF FAIL: Ask user \"Is Green LED blinking? Is USB connected?\" before blaming code.\n\nBOARD NAME FORMAT (REQUIRED):\n  • nrf52840dk/nrf52840 (NOT just \"nrf52840dk\")\n  • Find name: west boards | grep <chip>\n\nPROCESS CLEANUP (Crucial for stability):\n  • Before separate/new task: pkill -9 JLink; pkill -9 nrfutil; sleep 1\n  • PREVENT HANGS: Use \"timeout 60s\" for blocking commands (e.g. timeout 60s west flash)\n\nFORBIDDEN COMMANDS (WASTEFUL/FLAKY):\n  • DO NOT USE: hcitool, nRFConnectScanner, ble-scan (Host scanning fails in containers)\n  • DO NOT USE: nrfjprog --family --info (Use --ids instead)\n\nVERIFICATION STRATEGY (TRUST THE LOGS):\n  1. PRIMARY: RTT or UART logs showing boot & functionality.\n  2. SECONDARY: Ask user (\"Do you see LED blinking?\").\n  3. NEVER scan from the host machine.\n\nRTT LOGGING (THE \"PERFECT\" SEQUENCE):\n  1. Check RTT enabled: grep CONFIG_USE_SEGGER_RTT prj.conf\n  2. Cleanup: pkill -9 JLink; pkill -9 nrfutil; sleep 1\n  3. Connect: Use \"nRF RTT Terminal\" (VS Code) or JLinkExe (Plan B)\n  4. RESET (Crucial): In a NEW terminal, run: nrfjprog --reset -s <serial>\n  5. Observe: Watch RTT terminal immediately to catch boot logs\n  6. MISSING LOGS? Check prj.conf for CONFIG_LOG_DEFAULT_LEVEL=4 (Debug)\n\nUART LOGGING (Access via 'log_device' action):\n  • LIST PORTS: action=\"log_device\", operation=\"list\"\n  • PRE-FLIGHT TEST (2 sec): action=\"log_device\", operation=\"test\", port=\"/dev/ttyACM0\"\n  • CAPTURE LOGS: action=\"log_device\", operation=\"capture\", port=\"/dev/ttyACM0\", duration=\"30\", output=\"logs/\"\n  • MULTI-DEVICE: action=\"log_device\", operation=\"capture\", devices=\"central:/dev/ttyACM0,peripheral:/dev/ttyACM1\", duration=\"60\", output=\"logs/\"\n  • IF NO LOGS: Ask user \"Is USB connected? Try unplug/replug device\"\n\nFLASH PRIORITY:\n  1. Get devices: nrfjprog --ids\n  2. ONE device: timeout 60s west flash\n  3. MULTIPLE: timeout 60s west flash --snr <serial>\n  4. RECOVER: nrfjprog --recover (only if flash fails)\n\nBUILD DECISION TREE:\n  1. Check for build folder: ls build/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"no build\"\n  2. If NO build/: west build -b BOARD .\n  3. If build/ EXISTS:\n     - Fresh rebuild: west build -b BOARD . -p always\n     - Incremental: west build\n",
      "strict": false,
      "parameters": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "action": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Action: \"execute\" (generic cmd) or \"log_device\" (native logger)."
          },
          "command": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Command for action=\"execute\". E.g., \"west build ...\""
          },
          "operation": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Operation for action=\"log_device\": \"list\", \"test\", \"capture\"."
          },
          "port": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Serial port for log_device. E.g. /dev/ttyACM0"
          },
          "duration": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Log duration in seconds."
          },
          "devices": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Multi-device map: \"central:/dev/ttyACM0,...\""
          },
          "output": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Output directory for logs."
          }
        },
        "required": [
          "action"
        ],
        "additionalProperties": false
      }
    }
  },
